Final steps (with commands) to deploy site:

Start Gunicorn service  
sudo systemctl start gunicorn.socket  
sudo systemctl enable gunicorn.socket

Check Gunicorn Socket File  
sudo systemctl status gunicorn.socket  
sudo journalctl \-u gunicorn.socket

Test Socket Activation:  
curl \--unix-socket /run/gunicorn.sock localhost  
sudo systemctl status gunicorn  
sudo journalctl \-u gunicorn

Reload daemon and Gunicorn service (if gunicorn.service was configured incorrectly)  
sudo systemctl daemon-reload  
sudo systemctl restart gunicorn

Nginx setup (need ssl certificate/key for cdspeccollab.smcm.edu):  
Write server block in /etc/nginx/nginx.conf  
sudo nginx \-t  
sudo systemctl restart nginx

Check nginx logs:  
sudo less /var/log/nginx/access.log  
sudo less /var/log/nginx/error.log

Open firewall to 80/443 traffic (I believe this is different from port forwarding? Maybe ask OIT for specifics?):  
sudo ufw allow 'Nginx Full'
